<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-567] Can&apos;t immediately stop a TSimpleServer thread that is idle</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-567</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given the following conditions:&lt;br/&gt;
1) TSimpleServer running in its own thread&lt;br/&gt;
2) Server is idle (no clients connected)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If TSimpleServer::stop() is called, the server thread will not be stopped until the next client transaction occurs. You can&apos;t stop an idle server immediately.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the fix is to have TSimpleServer::stop() call serverTransport_-&amp;gt;interrupt(), just like the TThreadedServer does.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll submit a patch shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac OS X 10.5.8&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
